The Gauteng Provincial Command Council is giving its weekly update on the status of the Coronavirus pandemic. Premier David Makhura is also expected to speak about the investigation into the R125-million PPE tender scandal. JOHANNESBURG - The Gauteng Provincial Command Council gives an update on COVID-19 in the province. Gauteng is currently the epicentre of the COVID-19 pandemic. READ: Diko, Masuku to be subjected to Integrity Committee Gauteng Premier David Makhura will also brief the media on investigations by the Special Investigating Unit, including the specific investigation into the procurement of PPE in the Gauteng Department of Health. Meanwhile, the ANC Gauteng PEC has resolved that Presidency spokesperson, Khusela Diko and Health MEC Bandile Masuku be subjected to the Provincial Integrity Committee. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.